@NODE Introduction "Introduction"

 @{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

 Utilities Library is a library which contains many functions useful
 for performing different operations on strings and numbers. It contains
 functions for copying, comparing, inserting, reversing, etc. strings,
 few functions for comparing and generating random numbers and functions
 for converting string to numbers and numbers to strings.
@ENDNODE

@NODE Requirements "Requirements"

 @{b}@{u}Requirements@{ub}@{uu}

 The only thing that the library requires to work is Workbench 3.0 or
 higher.
@ENDNODE

@NODE History "History"

 @{b}@{u}History@{ub}@{uu}

 V1.2 (3)

 - seven new function have been added
 - StrToNum() function didn't change value of the error variable even
   if there was an error. Now it's fixed

 V1.1 (2)

 - two new functions have been added
 - autodoc is now avalaible in English
 - the documentation has been rewritten to AmigaGuide

 V1.0 (1)

 - first release
